{
  "texts": [
    "Given their extensive use, it is important to characterize their WCET to guarantee their safe application.",
    "Therefore, the focus of this thesis is on analyzing existing open-source real-time robotic algorithms, more specifically the collision detection algorithm.",
    "In the following, we first discuss the collision detection algorithm followed by three of its applications that are used to demonstrate and validate our proposed WCET methods discussed in Sections 4.2 and 4.3.",
    "Collision Detection AlgorithmIn our research, we employ the Flexible Collision Library (FCL) [102] for collision detection among various entities within dynamically changing environments.",
    "FCL presents a suite for addressing both collision and proximity queries across a spectrum of model representations, including rigid, articulated, and deformable objects, as well as point clouds."
  ]
}